  "prompt": "I told him I liked him and he didn't give me an actual answer! Help?",
  "response": "It can be confusing and frustrating when someone doesn't respond directly to your feelings. Here are a few steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Give It Time**: Sometimes, people need time to process their feelings. He may be surprised or unsure about how he feels in return.\n\n2. **Communicate**: If you're comfortable, you could bring it up again in a casual way. This might help you gauge his feelings more clearly.\n\n3. **Be Direct**: If you want a clearer answer, it might help to be direct again. You could say something like, \"I wanted to talk more about what I told you the other day. How do you feel about it?\"\n\n4. **Reflect on His Response**: Think about how he reacted when you told him. His body language, tone, and any non-verbal cues can provide insight into his feelings.\n\n5. **Consider Moving On**: If it becomes clear that he isn't interested or responsive, it might be best to focus on yourself and look for connections elsewhere.\n\n6. **Trust Your Instincts**: Ultimately, trust your feelings and instincts about the situation. If something feels off, it\u2019s okay to prioritize your emotional well-being.\n\nRemember, communication is key in any relationship, so don\u2019t hesitate to express your thoughts and feelings!",
